The article is a joint statement from the President of the United States and the President of Portugal, reaffirming the strong partnership between the two countries. They discussed ways to enhance their relationship, including through the U.S.-Portugal Bilateral Commission and partnerships between universities. They also discussed the world economic and financial situation and expressed support for Portugal's reform program. Both countries agreed to continue close cooperation within the U.N. Security Council on issues such as Syria, Libya, Middle East peace, and Iran. They reaffirmed their commitment to NATO and discussed ongoing NATO operations, particularly in Afghanistan. They also reviewed plans for the upcoming NATO Summit in Chicago in May 2012.